Select investments within the Redwood portfolio include:


Erickson Living Management, LLC
Initial Investment: 2010
Industry: Senior Living
Erickson Living Management, a leading developer and manager of continuing care retirement communities (CCRCs), manages 17 large campus-style communities in Colorado, Florida, Kansas, Maryland, Massachusetts, Michigan, New Jersey, Pennsylvania, Texas and Virginia. Its communities are home to more than 21,000 residents.



Premier Trailer Leasing
Initial Investment: 2016
Industry: Equipment Leasing
Premier Trailer Leasing is one of the largest trailer leasing and rental companies in the US. Premier maintains a fleet of over 32,000 trailers and specializes in long-term leasing and short-term rental services for over-the-road vans, flatbeds, refrigerated equipment and chassis.



Thompson Gas
Initial Investment: 2015
Industry: Retail Propane Distribution
Third generation family business that has grown to become one of the top 20 retail propane distributors in the US.



Tradepoint Atlantic, LLC
(formerly Sparrows Point Terminal, LLC)Initial Investment: 2014
Industry: Transportation Infrastructure
Tradepoint Atlantic, LLC is a multimodal terminal consisting of deep water berths, short-line railroad connecting to two Class I railroads, and direct interstate access. The 3,100 acre terminal is located in Baltimore County, Maryland and is the largest privately owned industrial site on the east coast.



Tarpon Towers, LLC
Initial Investment: 2015
Industry: Wireless Communication Infrastructure
Tarpon Towers is a wireless communications infrastructure company focused on the acquisition and development of telephony based towers. Tarpon's management team has financed, acquired and managed over 12,000 wireless communication towers across the country.



Redwood Rail, LLC
Initial Investment: 2015
Industry: Equipment Leasing
Redwood Rail offers rail equipment operating lease and finance solutions to industrial shippers and railroads in North America. Leasing structures include full service, net, per diem, sale leaseback and finance leases.

 
Beltway Capital Management, LLC
Initial Investment: 2007
Industry: Residential and Commercial Real Estate
Beltway Capital Management seeks to acquire commercial and industrial loans, residential mortgage loans and commercial real estate loans which, by reason of structure, location, industry and/or credit quality, are identified for sale by financial institutions.




